---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Short explanation of Marquis Ladybug and the Field Archive series.">
  <main class="page">
    <section class="section">
      <p class="kicker">About</p>
      <h1 class="page-title">てんとうむし侯爵</h1>
      <div class="text-block page-copy-block">
        <p>
          Marquis Ladybug is a small observation protocol inside Civilization OS. It does not treat the city as scenery; it reads railings, pipes, fences, glass, temporary panels, service entrances, warning paint, and human flow as local signals of a system still running.
        </p>
        <p>
          The city is an entropy machine held in place by maintenance. Heat load, routing, residue, repair, supply, and inspection leave marks on the surface. This archive records those marks as structure, not sentiment.
        </p>
        <p>
          Urban Structure Study follows fixed infrastructure and operating faces. Urban Drift follows light, motion, weathering, and human trace moving through that infrastructure. The photographs are not explanations; they are compressed observation logs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
